\begin_layout Subsubsection
Add Experiments with Other Kinds of Data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The only assumption about the data the proposed method makes, is that normally
 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{Q}$
\end_inset

 will be contained inside 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{P}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore it should be possible to detect anomalies in other kinds of data,
 e.g.
 EEG streams, or even non-medical data, like a data stream describing the
 power usage of a facility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Add experiments with Multidimensional Data-Streams
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The single dimensionality of an ECG is not a requirement of the method,
 thus, it is meaningful to make experiments using multidimensional time
 series, e.g.
 a time series combining ECG and EEG data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Modification of MGNG to use GNG-U
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Andreakis2009"

\end_inset

 the authors use a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

classical
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 version of GNG.
 A possible meaningful modification would be to use the GNG-U (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Fritzke1997"

\end_inset

) variant instead, to make the model adaptable to non-stationary distributions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Integration with Health Monitor
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The original reason for this thesis' idea was to provide a health monitor
 developed by the author (
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Crew activity monitor"
target "http://www.google-melange.com/gsoc/proposal/public/google/gsoc2014/mtambos/5649050225344512"

\end_inset

) with anomaly detection capabilities.
 Since this objective is not covered in the thesis' main goals, the author
 would like to put it amount the thesis' stretch goals.
 The idea would be to add to the health monitor an alarm to alert an overseer
 of possible health problems.
 It would require the integration with a GUI, also to be developed in Python.
\end_layout

